<br>
Just remember waaay back with Lava Bolt and Ice Comet.  Ice Comet was difficult to research and required some very tough to get components.  Lava Bolt was purchasable.<br>
<br>
Remember, many times when we do get bolt spells, for that level they are considerably powerful (however, not as much due to expansions).  As a 2000 damage nuke for 500 mana, expect to still lose a good chunk of bolts to blockage.  That seriously lowers the efficiency and usability of this nuke.  I seem to recall hearing that bolt spells were dead, due to their difficulty, cast time, and other factors.  Now since one is quite powerful, everyone wants to see it pushed back?  <br>
<br>
For those who are also concerned with its power for our class at its level, I remind you of level 34... look at our power at that level in comparison to other nuking classes..  This is nothing abnormal, and don't over estimate the power of this nuke (its huge, but aggro will be too, with no aggro avoidance other than spending some AA).  <br>
<br>
Historically, we've gotten our higher damage bolt spells, followed by our more easily to use shock/DD spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udurash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Durash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#333333>(10/17/02 11:19:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Keep it as-is</span><hr size=1> Bolt = no guarantee.<br>
