First of all, Shock of Black Steel is a better all aroung spell, because it has no line of sight issues. It costs less mana to cast, and has less aggro associated to it.<br>
<br>
Sure it isn't as big a bang as the bolt, but than a DD for a magician class never should be.<br>
<br>
Bolts should always hit harder, do to the restrictions of LOS etc..<br>
<br>
I think (and yes it is my opinoin) that if you had both, that Shock of Black Steel would be cast way more often than the bolt.<br>
<br>
Be honest, and those saying switch them, if BOTH were a level 61 spell, which one do you see casting more of?<br>
<br>
I know that I like the big boom, and aww factor, but I know I would be casting Shock of Black Steel te most.<br>
<br>
My question how many people used Seeking Flame when there was no Shock of Firery Blades, and opted for Char or Shock of Steel more often?<br>
<br>
I know I did, and yes I used seeking flame, but there were many times it wasn't freasable, and I didn't. Shock and Char were my mainstay nukes.<br>
<br>
I know a lot of mages, and it was usually the same. They broke out the bolt for fun, but Shock and Char were by far the most commonly used spells.<br>
<br>
By the way I make this post I should be in favor of the switch, and in a way I am, but I am also a gamer. I like the WOW aspect of this nuke. I also know when I hit level 63 that the wow factor wil have waned, and Shock of Black Steel will be one of my main stay nukes.<br>
<br>
So I will ask my question to those in favor of switching and those not in favor, and please be honest.<br>
<br>
Which nuke Talon's or Black Steel if you had both in your spell book do you think would become your mainstay nuke?<br>
<br>
I know my answer is Black Steel. <br>
